    "narrative": "The Austin Waves' offense is positioned for a high-ceiling output today, headlined by **Josh Lowe** (70.92) and **Gunnar Henderson** (67.58). **Josh Lowe** benefits significantly from the favorable matchup against Davis Martin (4.38 xERA) and the benefit of wind blowing out, providing a solid combination of power and stolen base upside. Similarly, **Gunnar Henderson** holds elite value; despite facing a 3.45 xERA arm, his 14% dynamic platoon boost and high-leverage spot in the order make him an essential engine for our daily Roto production. **Heliot Ramos** (64.53) and **Vladimir Guerrero Jr.** (63.07) also earn \"Strong\" status, with **Heliot Ramos** specifically benefiting from a high-upside matchup against Randy V\u00e1squez, who struggles with a 4.91 xERA.\n\nTactical edge-seeking drove several other start/sit decisions. **Sam Antonacci** (58.18) remains a high-floor start thanks to his leadoff role and an impressive 0.400 xwOBA, while **Nolan Schanuel** (59.87) is buoyed by favorable wind conditions. The most difficult bench decision involved **Coby Mayo** (40.71). He hovered near the starting threshold, but was ultimately pushed out by the higher floor provided by our current infield trio. While **Coby Mayo** offers intrigue, the optimizer prioritized the volume and platoon advantages held by the likes of **Liam Hicks** and **Miguel Vargas**. We continue to monitor the status of **Luis Robert Jr.**, who remains on the IL, while **Luis Garc\u00eda Jr.** remains benched due to a scheduling quirk. \n\nManagers should keep a close eye on official lineups, as our projections for **Drake Baldwin**, **Liam Hicks**, **Nolan Schanuel**, **Sam Antonacci**, **Gunnar Henderson**, **Miguel Vargas**, **Heliot Ramos**, **Josh Lowe**, **Kyle Tucker**, **Andy Pages**, **Jackson Merrill**, and **Vladimir Guerrero Jr.** are based on anticipated placement. Any late-breaking injury reports or defensive substitutions could shift these efficiency scores, particularly for **Drake Baldwin** and **Jackson Merrill**, whose values are sensitive to their respective order positions. Risks remain against elite arms like Logan Gilbert, but the overall landscape for the Waves suggests a productive day in the counting categories.",
